outputs:
{"answer": "Yes, it's generally good practice to have a mix of younger and older candidates when hiring. Older candidates may take longer to pick up the pace and might be more experienced with different types of tasks or challenges. This can be beneficial for your team as they will be able to work on complex projects together.

However, if you want to ensure that there are both younger and older candidates available to benefit from the different skill sets of each group, it's wise to have a balance. Older candidates might provide valuable experience in certain areas while younger candidates can bring fresh perspectives and experiences.

